Figure 4: 5G requirements dimensions
The 5G use cases demand very diverse and sometimes extreme requirements. It is anticipated that a single solution to satisfy all the extreme requirements at the same time may lead to over-specification and high cost. Nevertheless, several use cases are anticipated to be active concurrently in the same operator network, thus requiring a high degree of flexibility and scalability of the 5G network. In order to reflect their use-case dependency, the requirements are specified according to the “Use Case Categories” defined in the figure below. For each use case category, one set of requirement values is given, which is representative of the extreme use cases(s) in the category. As a result, satisfying the requirements of a category leads to satisfying the requirements of all the use cases in this category.

